1
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:53,780
Woo Gyeom, time to eat.

2
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,450
(Hematology and Regenerative Medicine)

3
00:00:57,050 --> 00:00:58,050
Lee Woo Gyeom!

4
00:01:45,130 --> 00:01:46,830
(Best Paper Award)

5
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,400
(Best Paper Presentation Award)

6
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:50,500
(Certificate of Award)

7
00:02:13,290 --> 00:02:16,530
You scared me!
Why didn't you say you were here?

8
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:19,500
I was about to, but you got startled
before I had a chance.

9
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:22,100
Also, I told you to...

10
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:26,070
turn off that metronome
before you sleep, didn't I?

11
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,910
It helps me focus better when I study.

12
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:31,710
(Lee Woo Gyeom gets accepted to
Guam Med School.)

13
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:33,210
- Mom.
- Yes?

14
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:34,540
Can't we take that down now?

15
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:37,250
It's on there just fine.
Why would we take it down?

16
00:02:37,610 --> 00:02:39,520
Have you forgotten that you're the pride
of this neighborhood?

17
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,420
Come on. The pride of the neighborhood?

18
00:02:44,490 --> 00:02:46,760
But whenever I come here,
it feels like time stands still.

19
00:02:49,290 --> 00:02:51,260
That place over there has been closed
for over ten years,

20
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,800
but it still looks exactly the same.

21
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:58,430
Sometimes, it's nice
when things don't change.

22
00:02:58,940 --> 00:03:00,070
You think so?

23
00:03:01,170 --> 00:03:04,440
- Mom, I'm heading out.
- Okay, dear. Be safe.

24
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:07,340
Oh, right. The contest results
are announced today, aren't they?

25
00:03:08,950 --> 00:03:11,450
Don't get your hopes up.
I probably didn't get it.

26
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:14,350
I'm sure you'll get good news,
so just you hurry home.

27
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:18,220
- I'll have a nice meal ready for you.
- Gosh, I told you not to bother.

28
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:19,760
I'm off.

29
00:03:23,230 --> 00:03:25,700
That concludes today's lecture.

30
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:28,700
- Thank you.
- You too.

31
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,870
Thank you, Professor.

32
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:32,970
Woo Gyeom. Let's go shoot some hoops.

33
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,640
Sorry, maybe later. I've got something
I have to finish today.

34
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,540
Gosh, you're relentless.

35
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,280
You always have to remind everyone
you're top of the class, don't you?

36
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:46,850
Woo Gyeom.

37
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:48,780
Could I have a word with you?

38
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,460
Our department has finally produced
a true talent.

39
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,360
You know Professor Han Sang Ho, right?

40
00:03:57,060 --> 00:04:01,130
He's the world's leading authority
on blood cancer and hematologic diseases.

41
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,270
Yes, I know of him.

42
00:04:04,230 --> 00:04:08,200
Professor Han Sang Ho himself
wants to meet you.

43
00:04:08,910 --> 00:04:09,940
We received a call from Chaeum.

44
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,010
No, really, Mom.

45
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:17,610
Professor Han Sang Ho read my thesis
and asked to see me. I'm telling you.

46
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:22,890
See? Didn't I tell you
you'd get good news?

47
00:04:23,490 --> 00:04:25,920
Congratulations! So you'll be home
early tonight, right?

48
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:30,230
This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance.
I have so many questions to ask him.

49
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,860
I'm going to the library
to organize my questions first, Mom.

50
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,300
Okay, but don't be too late.

51
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,830
I won't.

52
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:03,330
(The Final Choice)

53
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:13,940
Woo Gyeom.

54
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,910
Are you okay?

55
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:21,180
He's losing too much blood.
He needs a transfusion at a hospital.

56
00:05:21,810 --> 00:05:22,810
No.

57
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,550
That probably won't be possible.

58
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:28,450
My blood type...

59
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,890
is Rh null.

60
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:32,390
(Rh null: Can be donated to anyone,)

61
00:05:32,490 --> 00:05:33,920
(but can only be received
from Rh null donors)

62
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,470
(Chaeum Medical Group)

63
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:01,820
How much longer?

64
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:04,820
We'll be there in 20 minutes,
Mr. Chairman.

65
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,160
Director Ahn.

66
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:09,490
Sir?

67
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:12,960
So...

68
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,470
What do we do about Lee Woo Gyeom?

69
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:20,340
- Take him to the lab for the cure and...
- Right.

70
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:24,270
I know that's the right thing to do.

71
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:30,810
But seeing his disgustingly innocent face,
I'll want to kill him on the spot.

72
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:31,880
So how am I supposed to do that?

73
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:37,950
Don't you have an answer, Director Ahn?

74
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,720
You've spent your life killing people,
haven't you?

75
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:44,030
My apologies, sir.

76
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,200
Lee Woo Gyeom...

77
00:06:49,470 --> 00:06:52,670
Will he keep up the act even as he dies?
Or...

78
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:57,140
Or will he give up
and let his hideous true colors show...

79
00:06:58,140 --> 00:06:59,740
and beg me to spare his life?

80
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:05,780
Either way,

81
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,650
he's truly an infuriating man.

82
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:12,390
Yes, sir.

83
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:14,760
If we hadn't taken him in,
forget about finding a cure.

84
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:18,060
He'd have been found dead
in a ditch somewhere.

85
00:07:18,130 --> 00:07:21,260
So incredibly ungrateful.

86
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:24,730
Don't you agree?

87
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Yes, absolutely.

88
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,850
(Internal Report)

89
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:56,400
Didn't I tell you
not to put a call through?

90
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:03,240
Yes, Attorney General.

91
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,420
Reporter Jo?

92
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:24,390
- I'm fine.
- Wait, what happened?

93
00:08:25,730 --> 00:08:27,530
The people from Chaeum are
after Attorney Park.

94
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:28,830
What?

95
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,770
Why would they be after him?

96
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:32,270
It seems...

97
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:35,970
he helped Lee Woo Gyeom escape.

98
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:37,640
What?

99
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,710
You haven't heard from him at all?

100
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:43,450
- No.
- What about Prosecutor Cha's team?

101
00:08:44,110 --> 00:08:47,220
I went to Guam prosecutors this morning
with the files on Assemblyman Baek.

102
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:49,150
They're probably questioning him by now.

103
00:08:50,990 --> 00:08:53,320
- Are you okay?
- Go over there and get me the first aid.

104
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,820
The first aid?

105
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,420
- Just lie down.
- No, really. I'm okay.

106
00:09:31,890 --> 00:09:32,900
How's Min Seo?

107
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:43,410
Listen, Woo Gyeom.

108
00:09:44,210 --> 00:09:45,310
Why didn't you...

109
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:49,210
tell me everything from the start?
Not just Chairman Chae, but everything.

110
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:54,020
Did you forget grabbing me by the collar
the very first time we met?

111
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:59,050
And even when you knew
Sang Woo was completely cured,

112
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,960
you refused to believe me, didn't you?

113
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:03,860
Back then...

114
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,160
I know.

115
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,970
Back then,
all you could think about was Min Seo.

116
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:13,370
And you probably felt like
there wasn't anyone you could trust.

117
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,240
But it was the same for me.

118
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:21,240
Who would believe a serial killer
who murdered 17 people?

119
00:10:23,110 --> 00:10:26,050
And who would believe him if he claimed
he could cure the terminally ill?

120
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,920
Even I would have thought I was a lunatic.

121
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:38,290
You're still worried, aren't you?

122
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:43,230
That Min Seo might have a relapse someday.

123
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:49,540
No.

124
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,340
I believe you.

125
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:04,520
So you finally see
what I'm truly capable of.

126
00:11:05,450 --> 00:11:07,990
Think how much easier things would've been
if you had just believed me sooner.

127
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:11,560
Every time I was in court with you...

128
00:11:11,830 --> 00:11:13,660
Do you have any idea how frustrated I was?

129
00:11:15,970 --> 00:11:16,970
Is that so?

130
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:24,370
Woo Gyeom.

131
00:11:30,010 --> 00:11:31,010
Thank you.

132
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:33,420
For my Min Seo...

133
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:38,990
For saving my Min Seo.

134
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,260
Come on. Of course.

135
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:46,360
I was just doing
what I was supposed to do.

136
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,370
But Min Seo is really lucky.

137
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,500
She has such a great dad like you.

138
00:11:59,310 --> 00:12:00,310
You should...

139
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:03,550
get married and have kids of your own.

140
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:08,350
Then you'll understand
what it feels like to be a parent.

141
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,120
Do you think I could get married...

142
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:22,160
and have wonderful children like Min Seo?

143
00:12:28,170 --> 00:12:30,910
- You weren't planning on getting married?
- No, that's not it.

144
00:12:37,610 --> 00:12:38,650
Are you okay?

145
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,080
Yes, I'm fine.

146
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:48,660
But I should get going.

147
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,360
Why?

148
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:53,760
Chairman Chae will be here soon.

149
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,280
It's right here, counselor.

150
00:13:16,450 --> 00:13:19,090
This is where I first committed
to my entire plan.

151
00:13:30,130 --> 00:13:31,600
After my car accident,

152
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:34,600
I was taken to Chaeum Hospital.

153
00:13:39,310 --> 00:13:40,880
(Son)

154
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,550
He's an RH null patient in a coma.

155
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:48,220
Where is he from?

156
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,020
He's from Guam, Gyeonggi Province.

157
00:13:50,590 --> 00:13:52,520
And that's how I met Professor Han.

158
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:54,960
This is the patient who was just brought
to the research lab.

159
00:13:57,490 --> 00:14:01,960
To Chairman Chae Jeong Su,
obsessed with curing the incurable,

160
00:14:03,530 --> 00:14:05,470
I was the best test subject
he could ask for.

161
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,240
(Patient is negative for all antigens
in the Rh system.)

162
00:14:11,310 --> 00:14:13,110
(Test results determine
blood type is RH null.)

163
00:14:13,180 --> 00:14:14,840
(Rh null: Can be donated to anyone,)

164
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:16,180
(but can only be received
from Rh null donors)

165
00:14:17,150 --> 00:14:18,150
Proceed.

166
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,390
(Two weeks later)

167
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:29,460
Ma'am.

168
00:14:29,860 --> 00:14:32,330
It makes things difficult
when you keep coming in like this.

169
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:36,870
We're doing all we can to find your son.
We'll be in touch.

170
00:14:36,930 --> 00:14:39,900
It's been two weeks already
since Woo Gyeom disappeared.

171
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:44,770
If you haven't found a single lead,
then please, step up the investigation.

172
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:47,180
I'm sure you understand, Ma'am,

173
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:51,050
your son's case isn't the only one
we're working on,

174
00:14:51,210 --> 00:14:52,850
and there's a procedure for these things.

175
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:56,650
It's all going according to procedure,
so please, just wait.

176
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,450
Besides, at his age,

177
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:03,560
he could've just gone on a trip
with his girlfriend or some friends.

178
00:15:03,890 --> 00:15:04,890
You understand?

179
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:07,260
- Detective...
- We'll be in touch.

180
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,900
To find her son
who had suddenly disappeared,

181
00:15:12,730 --> 00:15:15,140
my mother worked tirelessly
day and night...

182
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,910
and started to retrace my steps.

183
00:15:17,970 --> 00:15:19,340
(Missing son)

184
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,180
(Missing son)

185
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,790
Even with no end in sight.

186
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:31,820
Even when the outcome was uncertain.

187
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,490
My mother never stopped.

188
00:15:43,330 --> 00:15:46,200
(Missing son)

189
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:54,140
(Missing son)

190
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:03,320
(Last seen:
Road near Guam University Central Library)

191
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:06,420
Ma'am, we've found your son.

192
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:10,830
He was the victim of a hit-and-run
and was taken to the hospital,

193
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:13,130
but they couldn't identify him
at the time,

194
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,070
so they say he was cremated,
and his ashes were interred at a facility.

195
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:20,470
To use me as a test subject,

196
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:24,240
Chaeum colluded with law enforcement
to falsely report my death.

197
00:16:24,810 --> 00:16:27,280
A few months after
she was told I had died,

198
00:16:27,810 --> 00:16:29,980
my mother, after endless inquiries,

199
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:33,280
found the dashcam footage
that captured my accident.

200
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,660
- Yes, that's the student.
- What?

201
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:47,630
When we arrived, he was unconscious,
so we transported him to the hospital.

202
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:49,930
And my route on the day of the accident,

203
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,600
and even testimonies from those
who transported me to Chaeum Hospital.

204
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:59,140
She began piecing the truth together,
to prepare a lawsuit against Chaeum.

205
00:16:59,210 --> 00:17:01,210
(Public Petitions Office)

206
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,280
(If Chaeum has nothing to hide,
reveal the truth of Woo Gyeom's death.)

207
00:17:03,350 --> 00:17:06,010
(At the time of the accident,
my son had his belongings and cell phone.)

208
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:29,200
There were others at the Chaeum Institute,
unclaimed, with fake identities like me.

209
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:34,810
And to keep the truth from getting out...

210
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:50,730
Eventually, Chairman Chae
even came after my mother.

211
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:30,100
And when Professor Han, who long led
the incurable disease research,

212
00:18:30,730 --> 00:18:32,630
failed to produce any significant results,

213
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,870
Chairman Chae,
feeling the pressure from investors,

214
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,270
brought in a new research team.

215
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,640
And to prevent Professor Han
from leaking any research data,

216
00:18:43,410 --> 00:18:45,310
he started having him watched
very closely.

217
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:51,490
Then, I miraculously woke up
during an experiment.

218
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:54,490
And Professor Han, unable to take
the pressure from Chairman Chae,

219
00:18:54,790 --> 00:18:56,630
ended up escaping with me.

220
00:18:56,890 --> 00:18:57,890
Lee Woo Gyeom.

221
00:19:01,930 --> 00:19:05,300
You need to lay low for a while
until I find an investor.

222
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,270
It won't take long, so just trust me.

223
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:12,940
I'll see this through to the end
and make sure you get cured.

224
00:19:32,130 --> 00:19:33,130
Woo Gyeom.

225
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:36,260
Where have you been?

226
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:38,500
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

227
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,040
Mom.

228
00:20:45,730 --> 00:20:47,040
(Person swept away in Busan
moments before rescue)

229
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:59,010
(Siding with the people,
not the prosecution)

230
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,120
(Former prosecutor-turned-lawyer
Park Han Jun's human rights activism)

231
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:04,850
At the very least, I can cure Min Seo.

232
00:21:05,620 --> 00:21:08,760
How do you even know my daughter's name?

233
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:14,760
(The Iron Fist,
Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon of the Guam DPO)

234
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:16,200
(Secures max sentences
in violent crime trials)

235
00:21:17,430 --> 00:21:18,430
It's a pleasure to meet you.

236
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,400
Prosecutor Cha Yi Yeon.

237
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:27,210
(When the Press Is Our Last Shield)

238
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,510
(When the Press Is Our Last Shield,
by Reporter Jo Woo Cheol)

239
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,250
What's the deal
between you and Lee Woo Gyeom?

240
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:36,020
About a week before he was arrested?
Lee Woo Gyeom contacted me directly.

241
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:39,690
At first, I thought he was a lunatic too.

242
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:43,260
But when a survivor shows up
right in front of you...

243
00:21:44,060 --> 00:21:46,330
I just thought, "This must be fate,"
and went with it.

244
00:22:06,650 --> 00:22:08,880
(Chaeum Med Center's completion ceremony
for Chaeum Research Institute)

245
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:46,620
Gosh, you got here fast.

246
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:06,880
- Don't you think this pin suits me?
- Of course, sir.

247
00:23:07,540 --> 00:23:08,540
You look absolutely fantastic, sir.

248
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:09,880
Yes.

249
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,850
Chairman Chae.
He's meeting with Director Oh right now.

250
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:51,220
The one who started all of this...

251
00:23:52,390 --> 00:23:54,220
wasn't me. It was Chairman Chae.

252
00:23:55,620 --> 00:23:57,290
Now, if Chairman Chae were to disappear...

253
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:05,100
Don't you think the serial killer
who killed 17 should disappear as well?

254
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:09,600
Woo Gyeom.
What are you thinking right now?

255
00:24:16,980 --> 00:24:17,980
Counselor.

256
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:38,170
Han Jun was with Lee Woo Gyeom?

257
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:41,570
Seriously,
why are you just telling me this now?

258
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:47,440
So where are Lee Woo Gyeom
and Han Jun now?

259
00:24:52,780 --> 00:24:55,480
Yes, I understand. Okay.

260
00:24:56,890 --> 00:24:57,890
Ma'am.

261
00:24:58,950 --> 00:25:01,020
The detectives at Guam Station
found Detective Gong's location.

262
00:25:01,890 --> 00:25:05,060
- I'm off. Please handle things here.
- Yes, ma'am.

263
00:25:06,660 --> 00:25:07,660
Let's go.

264
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,400
Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

265
00:25:50,370 --> 00:25:52,610
It looks like your little outing
is about to end.

266
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:54,780
How does it feel?

267
00:25:56,980 --> 00:25:57,980
Mr. Chae Jeong Su.

268
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,850
What do you think you're doing?

269
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:04,190
Counselor.

270
00:26:04,990 --> 00:26:06,820
Shouldn't I be the one
asking the questions?

271
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:09,860
We're just here to retrieve Lee Woo Gyeom,

272
00:26:09,860 --> 00:26:12,390
the serial killer
who is under Chaeum's care.

273
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:15,430
So why are you here with him, Counselor?

274
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:19,370
Wait. Did you perhaps help
Lee Woo Gyeom escape?

275
00:26:21,670 --> 00:26:22,670
Why?

276
00:26:24,510 --> 00:26:25,510
Because of your daughter?

277
00:26:28,180 --> 00:26:31,980
Gosh, this is a complete mess.
What is the world coming to?

278
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,320
You and Mr. Lee...

279
00:26:36,380 --> 00:26:39,120
Don't you feel
any ounce of guilt or responsibility...

280
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:42,760
for the terminally ill patients
around the world waiting for the cure?

281
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:46,260
This is no time for you two
to be acting like this.

282
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:52,470
A father who throws everything away
just to save his one daughter...

283
00:26:53,170 --> 00:26:57,210
and a son who whines about his dead mom.
It's pathetic, really.

284
00:27:01,780 --> 00:27:03,680
Woo Gyeom!

285
00:27:10,620 --> 00:27:13,350
What are you doing?
What are you doing, Mr. Shin Ho Chang?

286
00:27:13,990 --> 00:27:17,260
I said, "What are you doing?"
What? What? You son of a gun.

287
00:27:19,090 --> 00:27:22,860
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry? You're sorry?

288
00:27:34,310 --> 00:27:35,310
Director Ahn.

289
00:27:39,510 --> 00:27:41,150
This is unacceptable.

290
00:27:42,380 --> 00:27:44,550
How on earth do you train your staff?

291
00:27:46,220 --> 00:27:47,220
That's mine.

292
00:27:48,490 --> 00:27:49,490
I said it's mine.

293
00:27:50,690 --> 00:27:53,900
I can barely stop myself from killing him
right this second...

294
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:56,860
So why would you harm a test subject
whose life is already hanging by a thread?

295
00:27:57,170 --> 00:27:58,170
Why?

296
00:28:08,410 --> 00:28:09,710
Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom, are you all right?

297
00:28:10,550 --> 00:28:12,610
I'm so sorry.
My team made a terrible mistake.

298
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:14,720
I'm truly sorry.

299
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:17,850
But...

300
00:28:21,420 --> 00:28:24,190
Everyone makes mistakes from time to time.

301
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:27,100
Just like everything you've done to me
up until now.

302
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:31,230
Let's forgive and forget.
Let's focus on the bigger picture now.

303
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,400
Just like we did at the start.

304
00:28:35,470 --> 00:28:39,040
Let's go back to Chaeum and start over.

305
00:28:40,210 --> 00:28:44,910
So patients with incurable diseases
can get a new lease on life.

306
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,610
How many people do you have to save
to make it all okay?

307
00:29:18,850 --> 00:29:22,480
How many more do we have to save
to undo what you've done?

308
00:29:23,820 --> 00:29:26,590
Have you ever considered saving more lives
than the ones you took?

309
00:29:27,690 --> 00:29:29,290
You're not supposed to be like this.

310
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:34,030
Of all people, you should know better
than to do this.

311
00:30:04,730 --> 00:30:06,990
That list of test subjects
Professor Han had.

312
00:30:07,460 --> 00:30:09,260
You were the one who had it, weren't you?

313
00:30:11,470 --> 00:30:12,470
Still, what a relief.

314
00:30:12,970 --> 00:30:14,640
That's the property of Chaeum, you know.

315
00:30:16,070 --> 00:30:17,840
Why are you going to such lengths?

316
00:30:18,540 --> 00:30:20,880
You were a victim of your own father too.

317
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:24,850
You know the feeling of being
experimented on, so why?

318
00:30:25,950 --> 00:30:26,950
A victim?

319
00:30:30,180 --> 00:30:31,650
I'm not a victim.

320
00:30:34,090 --> 00:30:36,460
You seem to be misunderstanding something,
Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

321
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:47,070
(Chaeum Medical Center)

322
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:17,530
The experiment is progressing,
but we lack a suitable test subject, so...

323
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:36,480
I...

324
00:31:37,890 --> 00:31:40,660
I chose to become a test subject.

325
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:43,460
The son becomes the ingredient,

326
00:31:43,990 --> 00:31:46,460
and the father researches a cure.

327
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:51,300
An age will come
when Chaeum controls life and death.

328
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:57,270
Don't you see what a great honor it is
to be a test subject?

329
00:32:08,450 --> 00:32:09,450
Isn't that magnificent?

330
00:32:10,020 --> 00:32:11,750
A challenge no one has ever accomplished.

331
00:32:12,150 --> 00:32:16,760
It started with Chaeum's first chairman,
my father, Professor Chae Jeong Hun.

332
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:18,360
And we're almost there, Mr. Lee Woo Gyeom.

333
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,090
The day we can use your blood...

334
00:32:21,130 --> 00:32:24,100
and Chaeum's technology
to create the cure...

335
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:29,900
and show the world Chaeum's greatness.
That day is almost here!

336
00:32:37,210 --> 00:32:38,210
Woo Gyeom.

337
00:32:53,590 --> 00:32:56,330
Woo Gyeom. Don't. Just stop, okay?

338
00:32:57,870 --> 00:32:59,400
He can't get away with this.

339
00:33:01,300 --> 00:33:02,440
If I don't stop him now,

340
00:33:03,070 --> 00:33:05,410
- there will be more monsters like me.
- Woo Gyeom!

341
00:33:07,540 --> 00:33:09,140
I'll handle this. You should leave, sir.

342
00:33:45,810 --> 00:33:46,850
Lee Woo Gyeom!

343
00:33:47,380 --> 00:33:48,380
Stop.

344
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:04,230
You're a little late today, Prosecutor.

345
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:06,200
That's enough now.

346
00:34:06,970 --> 00:34:09,340
We already have testimony about
Chairman Chae's illegal experiments,

347
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:10,540
- It's all right, Prosecutor Cha.
- so...

348
00:34:13,410 --> 00:34:15,240
It's already too late for me as well.

349
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:26,090
Han Jun!

350
00:34:27,660 --> 00:34:29,560
Counselor.

351
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:38,800
Stay back!

352
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,440
Woo Gyeom.

353
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:47,170
Let's just stop.

354
00:34:48,940 --> 00:34:50,640
I know how wronged you feel.
How furious you are.

355
00:34:53,150 --> 00:34:54,180
I know it all too well.

356
00:34:55,820 --> 00:34:59,020
This time, I swear I'll do
whatever it takes to save you.

357
00:35:01,420 --> 00:35:02,420
So please, let's stop.

358
00:35:04,290 --> 00:35:05,290
For both our sakes,

359
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,930
this is just too much, man.

360
00:35:20,570 --> 00:35:21,580
Woo Gyeom.

361
00:35:28,420 --> 00:35:29,420
I'm glad.

362
00:35:31,290 --> 00:35:32,290
Prosecutor.

363
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,960
Please take good care of my lawyer for me.

364
00:37:02,310 --> 00:37:05,980
Police reported an unexpected incident
during the arrest of Lee Woo Gyeom,

365
00:37:06,250 --> 00:37:10,220
and that they had to discharge a firearm
to secure the scene.

366
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,590
(Chairman Chae Jeong Su
arrested at the scene.)

367
00:37:11,750 --> 00:37:16,260
Additionally, Chairman Chae Jeong Su
of the Chaeum Medical Group was arrested.

368
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:19,260
An investigation is underway into his role
in leading illegal medical experiments...

369
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:23,530
and his attempts to cover up
the resulting patient deaths.

370
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:43,320
I'm Cha Yi Yeon
from Criminal Division one.

371
00:37:43,850 --> 00:37:48,060
This case involves illegal medical crimes
that were perpetrated for years,

372
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:51,030
by gambling with the lives
of nameless victims.

373
00:37:53,560 --> 00:37:55,830
Lee Woo Gyeom asked me
to give this to you.

374
00:38:00,670 --> 00:38:01,670
What is this?

375
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:05,610
Counselor, take this.

376
00:38:10,210 --> 00:38:11,810
Chairman Chae and Professor Han
experimented...

377
00:38:12,450 --> 00:38:14,480
on people with no kin and killed them.

378
00:38:15,620 --> 00:38:19,120
This is the personal information
of those 223 victims.

379
00:38:21,420 --> 00:38:24,390
To date, the number of deaths at
the Chaeum Medical research institute...

380
00:38:24,390 --> 00:38:26,060
has reached a staggering total of 223.

381
00:38:26,260 --> 00:38:29,630
In response, the Prosecution
has arrested all parties...

382
00:38:29,930 --> 00:38:33,630
who committed these unforgivable crimes
under the shadow of money and power.

383
00:38:34,340 --> 00:38:37,810
We promise to enforce the law
without a shred of leniency.

384
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:43,240
Makes it all worthwhile.

385
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:56,590
Where are you headed today,
Prosecutor Cha?

386
00:38:59,190 --> 00:39:00,790
Since I received something
from Lee Woo Gyeom,

387
00:39:01,830 --> 00:39:04,060
I feel I should go pay my respects.

388
00:39:04,530 --> 00:39:06,630
You two should head home early
and get some rest today.

389
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:09,640
No, that's okay.
We must first identify the victims...

390
00:39:09,700 --> 00:39:10,700
Prosecutor Cha.

391
00:39:11,270 --> 00:39:12,510
Let's go this way. This way.

392
00:39:12,810 --> 00:39:16,040
- The entrance is full of reporters.
- Seriously.

393
00:39:16,110 --> 00:39:17,610
It'll be a pain
if the reporters catch you.

394
00:39:19,780 --> 00:39:21,580
(Guam District Prosecutors' Office,
Public Service Center)

395
00:39:23,820 --> 00:39:24,820
Prosecutor Cha.

396
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:27,990
Get home safe. We'll see you tomorrow.

397
00:39:57,690 --> 00:40:00,290
We've secured both witnesses and evidence.

398
00:40:00,890 --> 00:40:01,960
So why on earth?

399
00:40:02,890 --> 00:40:06,330
Why are you still protecting Chairman Chae
to the very end?

400
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:07,760
Why?

401
00:40:11,300 --> 00:40:13,900
The Chaeum case,
the one Baek bribed me to ignore...

402
00:40:14,970 --> 00:40:17,770
is on a whole other level
than what you're imagining.

403
00:40:20,370 --> 00:40:21,440
Hey, Oh Hyeon Deuk.

404
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:23,840
Have you lost your mind?

405
00:40:27,350 --> 00:40:31,690
You backstabbing son of a gun!
Did you forget who made you what you are?

406
00:40:31,890 --> 00:40:35,120
Did you?
You think I'm going to let this slide?

407
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:37,730
Let go!

408
00:40:38,590 --> 00:40:39,590
Let go of me!

409
00:40:44,260 --> 00:40:45,970
I'll tell you everything.

410
00:40:47,030 --> 00:40:48,440
About Chairman Chae and Assemblyman Baek.

411
00:40:48,770 --> 00:40:51,810
The start of the Lee Woo Gyeom incidents,
the people involved,

412
00:40:52,910 --> 00:40:55,240
and every single thing you suspect,
down to the last detail.

413
00:40:59,180 --> 00:41:01,580
Why the sudden change of heart?

414
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,180
I heard you met with Chief Pyo.

415
00:41:05,090 --> 00:41:06,490
You must have a rough idea then.

416
00:41:08,190 --> 00:41:09,320
Chairman Cha.

417
00:41:10,620 --> 00:41:11,630
Your father...

418
00:41:12,590 --> 00:41:13,790
asked me to tell you...

419
00:41:15,260 --> 00:41:16,600
to stop here.

420
00:41:18,270 --> 00:41:19,270
Director Oh.

421
00:41:20,330 --> 00:41:21,370
I...

422
00:41:21,970 --> 00:41:25,270
I'm not a three-year-old child
who has to listen to her dad.

423
00:41:26,340 --> 00:41:28,780
If I were going to do this half-heartedly,
I never would've started.

424
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:33,310
From now on, just tell me the facts,
exactly like you are now.

425
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:38,220
Whoever was involved, whatever they did...
Don't leave a single thing out.

426
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:42,520
All right.

427
00:41:43,420 --> 00:41:46,090
Then I'll start recording now.

428
00:41:54,230 --> 00:41:55,240
Yi Yeon.

429
00:42:26,870 --> 00:42:28,740
If anything should happen to me,

430
00:42:31,870 --> 00:42:34,240
open the metronome in my studio.

431
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:38,180
Inside, you'll find the first treatment
I ever developed.

432
00:42:41,980 --> 00:42:44,020
The choice is now yours, Counselor.

433
00:42:47,020 --> 00:42:49,020
Whether developing the final treatment...

434
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:51,790
to save countless lives...

435
00:42:53,230 --> 00:42:56,700
Or if that in turn will cause
countless deaths...

436
00:42:58,270 --> 00:43:00,000
is something no one on Earth
can possibly know.

437
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:18,090
(No caller ID)

438
00:43:23,460 --> 00:43:25,590
- Hello?
- It's me.

439
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:36,000
I trust you've been well.

440
00:43:40,140 --> 00:43:41,140
Counselor.

441
00:43:41,140 --> 00:43:42,910
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
